wfDhcpSvrDelete.name: wfDhcpSvrDelete
wfDhcpSvrDelete.description: Created/Deleted: if set to Deleted, the DHCP server is removed from this platform.

wfDhcpSvrDisable.name: wfDhcpSvrDisable
wfDhcpSvrDisable.description: Enable/Disable: controls whether the DHCP server is enabled or disabled on this platform.

wfDhcpSvrMgrIpAddr.name: wfDhcpSvrMgrIpAddr
wfDhcpSvrMgrIpAddr.description: IP Address of the NetID DHCP Server Manager serving this platform instance.

wfDhcpSvrMgrTcpPort.name: wfDhcpSvrMgrTcpPort
wfDhcpSvrMgrTcpPort.description: The remote TCP port number over which the DHCP Server communicates with the NetID DHCP Server Manager.

wfDhcpSvrConfDetPings.name: wfDhcpSvrConfDetPings
wfDhcpSvrConfDetPings.description: Number of ping attempts that should be made to a prospective client IP address to detect a possible conflict before declaring it unused and therefore available.

wfDhcpSvrIcmpTmo.name: wfDhcpSvrIcmpTmo
wfDhcpSvrIcmpTmo.description: Amount of time, in milliseconds, to wait for a conflict detection ping to time out.

wfDhcpSvrSafeModeDisable.name: wfDhcpSvrSafeModeDisable
wfDhcpSvrSafeModeDisable.description: Specifies whether the DHCP Server should wait until it gets acknowledgment of successful commitment of a lease from the NetID DHCP Server Manager before sending a lease-granted acknowledgment back to the DHCP Client. If set to Enabled, the DHCP Server will wait for the NetID DHCP Server Manager to confirm successful commit. If set to Disabled, the DHCP Server will immediately send back a lease-granted acknowledgement to the DHCP Client, without awaiting a commit-succeeded acknowledgment from the NetID DHCP Server Manager.

wfDhcpSvrMaxPendingLeases.name: wfDhcpSvrMaxPendingLeases
wfDhcpSvrMaxPendingLeases.description: Maximum number of lease requests to the DHCP Server which are pending commitment by the NetID DHCP Server Manager. Once there are wfDhcpSvrMaxPendingLeases lease requests pending, all new lease requests will be dropped until the number of requests pending decreases to wfDhcpSvrMaxPendingLeases/2.

wfDhcpSvrDebugLevel.name: wfDhcpSvrDebugLevel
wfDhcpSvrDebugLevel.description: Maximum debug level for optional debug messages from the DHCP Server. Normally, only messages with a debug level of 0 will be logged. The higher this attribute is made (up to a maximum of 10), the more messages will be logged. Since the logging of additional information can fill the log very rapidly and cause loss of other information, this attribute should only be changed to resolve critical problems.

wfDhcpSvrMgrLocIpAddr.name: wfDhcpSvrMgrLocIpAddr
wfDhcpSvrMgrLocIpAddr.description: IP Address the DHCP Server uses to identify itself to NetID DHCP Server Manager serving this platform instance. Should correspond to an actual local interface address on the router.

wfDhcpSvrIntfTable.name: wfDhcpSvrIntfTable
wfDhcpSvrIntfTable.description: This table contains per-interface status information for DHCP Server operation.

wfDhcpSvrIntfEntry.name: wfDhcpSvrIntfEntry
wfDhcpSvrIntfEntry.description: A DHCP Server network interface status description.

wfDhcpSvrIntfState.name: wfDhcpSvrIntfState
wfDhcpSvrIntfState.description: The state of the DHCP Server on this network interface.

wfDhcpSvrIntfPendLsCnt.name: wfDhcpSvrIntfPendLsCnt
wfDhcpSvrIntfPendLsCnt.description: Number of DHCP leases pending commitment by the NetID Server Manager on this network interface.

wfDhcpSvrIntfActLsCnt.name: wfDhcpSvrIntfActLsCnt
wfDhcpSvrIntfActLsCnt.description: Number of DHCP leases currently active and committed by the NetID Server Manager on this network interface.

wfDhcpSvrIntfCommits.name: wfDhcpSvrIntfCommits
wfDhcpSvrIntfCommits.description: Number of Commit requests made by the DHCP Server for clients on this network interface.

wfDhcpSvrIntfCommitFails.name: wfDhcpSvrIntfCommitFails
wfDhcpSvrIntfCommitFails.description: Number of Commit-failed responses to the DHCP Server for clients on this network interface.

wfDhcpSvrIntfCommitTmos.name: wfDhcpSvrIntfCommitTmos
wfDhcpSvrIntfCommitTmos.description: Number of times the NetID DHCP Server Manager did not respond to a commit request from the DHCP Server for clients on this network interface.

wfDhcpSvrIntfIllegPkts.name: wfDhcpSvrIntfIllegPkts
wfDhcpSvrIntfIllegPkts.description: Number of DHCP packets with no legal type sent to the DHCP Server for clients on this network interface.

wfDhcpSvrIntfDiscovers.name: wfDhcpSvrIntfDiscovers
wfDhcpSvrIntfDiscovers.description: Number of DISCOVER packets sent to DHCP Server by clients on this network interface.

wfDhcpSvrIntfBadDiscovers.name: wfDhcpSvrIntfBadDiscovers
wfDhcpSvrIntfBadDiscovers.description: Number of badly-formed DISCOVER packets sent to DHCP Server for clients on this network interface.

wfDhcpSvrIntfReassgnLeases.name: wfDhcpSvrIntfReassgnLeases
wfDhcpSvrIntfReassgnLeases.description: Number of client requests for leases already reassigned to another client of DHCP Server on this network interface.

wfDhcpSvrIntfNoFreeLeases.name: wfDhcpSvrIntfNoFreeLeases
wfDhcpSvrIntfNoFreeLeases.description: Number of times DHCP Server had no leases available to offer a client in response to a DHCPDISCOVER request on this network interface.

wfDhcpSvrIntfDropdLeaseRqs.name: wfDhcpSvrIntfDropdLeaseRqs
wfDhcpSvrIntfDropdLeaseRqs.description: Number of DHCP client requests for a lease on this interface which were dropped by the DHCP Server because the total number of leases pending commitment exceeded the threshhold for accepting new leases at the time the client made the request.

wfDhcpSvrIntfOffers.name: wfDhcpSvrIntfOffers
wfDhcpSvrIntfOffers.description: Number of offers (DHCPOFFER messages) sent out by DHCP Server for clients on this network interface.

wfDhcpSvrIntfRequests.name: wfDhcpSvrIntfRequests
wfDhcpSvrIntfRequests.description: Number of DHCPREQUEST packets sent to DHCP Server by clients on this network interface.

wfDhcpSvrIntfBadRequests.name: wfDhcpSvrIntfBadRequests
wfDhcpSvrIntfBadRequests.description: Number of badly-formed DHCPREQUEST packets sent to DHCP Server by clients on this network interface.

wfDhcpSvrIntfReleases.name: wfDhcpSvrIntfReleases
wfDhcpSvrIntfReleases.description: Number of DHCPRELEASE packets sent to DHCP Server by clients on this network interface.

wfDhcpSvrIntfBadReleases.name: wfDhcpSvrIntfBadReleases
wfDhcpSvrIntfBadReleases.description: Number of badly-formed DHCPRELEASE packets sent to DHCP Server by clients on this network interface.

wfDhcpSvrIntfDeclines.name: wfDhcpSvrIntfDeclines
wfDhcpSvrIntfDeclines.description: Number of DHCPDECLINE packets sent to DHCP Server by clients on this network interface.

wfDhcpSvrIntfBadDeclines.name: wfDhcpSvrIntfBadDeclines
wfDhcpSvrIntfBadDeclines.description: Number of badly-formed DHCPDECLINE packets sent to DHCP Server by clients on this network interface.

wfDhcpSvrIntfInforms.name: wfDhcpSvrIntfInforms
wfDhcpSvrIntfInforms.description: Number of DHCPINFORM packets sent to DHCP Server by non-lease clients on this network interface.

wfDhcpSvrIntfBadInforms.name: wfDhcpSvrIntfBadInforms
wfDhcpSvrIntfBadInforms.description: Number of badly-formed DHCPINFORM packets sent to DHCP Server by non-lease clients on this network interface.

wfDhcpSvrIntfAddrConflict.name: wfDhcpSvrIntfAddrConflict
wfDhcpSvrIntfAddrConflict.description: Number of times the conflict detection phase of DHCP lease assignment detected a host using the IP address the DHCP Server was working to assign. This normally indicates that the detected host is using an IP address which it doesn't own.

wfDhcpSvrLeaseTable.name: wfDhcpSvrLeaseTable
wfDhcpSvrLeaseTable.description: This table contains per-interface, per-lease status information for DHCP Server operation.

wfDhcpSvrLeaseState.name: wfDhcpSvrLeaseState
wfDhcpSvrLeaseState.description: The current state of a lease. It may be committed in the NetID Server Manager, pending commitment, or pending with an already failed or timed-out commitment attempt.

wfDhcpSvrLeaseRetries.name: wfDhcpSvrLeaseRetries
wfDhcpSvrLeaseRetries.description: Number of lease commit retries for this lease either because of reported commit fail from NetID Server Manager or because of timeout on commit request. Zero if lease pending or committed.

wfDhcpSvrLeaseExpir.name: wfDhcpSvrLeaseExpir
wfDhcpSvrLeaseExpir.description: Time when lease will expire. Expressed as number of seconds since beginning of January 1, 1970.

wfDhcpSvrLeaseDuration.name: wfDhcpSvrLeaseDuration
wfDhcpSvrLeaseDuration.description: Agreed-upon duration of lease, in seconds.

wfDhcpSvrLeaseHwId.name: wfDhcpSvrLeaseHwId
wfDhcpSvrLeaseHwId.description: Hardware identifier of client holding the lease.

wfDhcpSvrLeaseClId.name: wfDhcpSvrLeaseClId
wfDhcpSvrLeaseClId.description: Client identifier of client holding the lease.

wfDhcpSvrLeaseFqdn.name: wfDhcpSvrLeaseFqdn
wfDhcpSvrLeaseFqdn.description: Fully qualified domain name of client holding the lease, for DNS update management.
